## 3. OBSERVATIONS (Positive Aspects)

### 3.1 Strong Architecture Patterns
- Circuit breaker pattern correctly applied to prevent CBILL overload
- Exponential backoff with jitter (line 194) is production-grade
- Sharding strategy for status GSI (line 116) prevents hot partitions

### 3.2 LGPD Awareness
- HMAC tokenization approach is correct for preventing brute-force attacks
- TTL strategy (90 days DynamoDB → 6 years S3 Glacier) aligns with Brazilian retention requirements
- Separate `error_category` (BUSINESS vs INFRASTRUCTURE) enables proper circuit breaker behavior

### 3.3 Operational Excellence
- Comprehensive alarm coverage (lines 265-271)
- Time-to-resolution metric enables SLA tracking
- Phased implementation reduces deployment risk

### 3.4 Cost Optimization
- On-demand DynamoDB billing appropriate for unpredictable workload
- S3 Glacier lifecycle correctly applied
- EventBridge Scheduler more cost-effective than CloudWatch Events

---

